video.title: House of Cards
video.synopsis: A ruthless politician will stop at nothing to conquer Washington, D.C., in this Emmy and Golden Globe-winning political drama.

episodes.synopsis: When the newly elected President reneges on a promise, Francis and Claire decide to sever all allegiances and toss the rules out the window.
episodes.title: Chapter 1

episodes.synopsis: Francis uses a young reporter, Zoe Barnes, to spin a story that puts the White House on its heels. Claire makes a cold-blooded move at work.
episodes.title: Chapter 2

episodes.synopsis: Francis must leave union negotiations to deal with a crisis in his home district. Zoe negotiates the politics of being a journalist on the rise.
episodes.title: Chapter 3

episodes.synopsis: Francis shakes down the Congressional leadership. Peter Russo must choose between politics and family.
episodes.title: Chapter 4

episodes.synopsis: Francis's fight over the Education Bill threatens Claire's own ambitions. Zoe mixes work and play.
episodes.title: Chapter 5

episodes.synopsis: Francis strikes back at the striking teachers. Claire is caught off guard by a deathbed confession.
episodes.title: Chapter 6

episodes.synopsis: Francis wins a major battle, but doesn't pause to rest on his laurels. Peter must face his past. Stamper hushes a secret.
episodes.title: Chapter 7

episodes.synopsis: Francis is honored at his alma mater, while Peter returns to Philly. Both men tackle unfinished business.
episodes.title: Chapter 8

episodes.synopsis: Russo hits the road with V.P. Matthews. Francis and Stamper try to whip up support in Congress. Claire looks out for herself.
episodes.title: Chapter 9

episodes.synopsis: Rebellion on all fronts. Claire defies Francis, Zoe finds comfort in someone new, and Peter makes an ultimatum.
episodes.title: Chapter 10

episodes.synopsis: Claire fuels an old flame. Peter wrestles with his demons. Francis crosses the point of no return.
episodes.title: Chapter 11

episodes.synopsis: Francis must make an unforeseen detour. Zoe, Lucas and Janine get closer to the truth.
episodes.title: Chapter 12

episodes.synopsis: Francis scrambles to keep his plan on track. Claire is haunted by choices old and new. Zoe poses a serious threat.
episodes.title: Chapter 13

episodes.synopsis: The Underwoods tackle two threats that could bring their plans to ruin. Francis grooms his replacement as Whip. Claire goes on the offensive.
episodes.title: Chapter 14

episodes.synopsis: Francis puts China in the cross-hairs. Claire confronts a painful trauma from her past. Lucas Goodwin presses for the truth.
episodes.title: Chapter 15

episodes.synopsis: Tension rises between Francis and Raymond Tusk as the situation with China deteriorates. A battle in the Senate pits Francis against the Republicans.
episodes.title: Chapter 16

episodes.synopsis: A terror scare at the Capitol traps Francis with a resentful Donald Blythe. Claire gives a live interview that rocks the media.
episodes.title: Chapter 17

episodes.synopsis: Francis back-channels with a Chinese billionaire. Lucas uses extreme measures to expose the Vice President. A shadowy figure joins Team Underwood.
episodes.title: Chapter 18

episodes.synopsis: Amidst an energy crisis, Francis and Tusk end their shaky alliance. Lucas must make a difficult choice. Stamper grows closer to Rachel.
episodes.title: Chapter 19

episodes.synopsis: Despite some friction, the Walkers deepen their friendship with the Underwoods. But it's all-out war between Francis and Tusk.
episodes.title: Chapter 20

episodes.synopsis: The war with Tusk intensifies. Claire influences Tricia Walker politically and domestically. Francis has a show-down with Linda Vasquez.
episodes.title: Chapter 21

episodes.synopsis: Things get personal when Tusk blindsides the Underwoods with a scandal. Freddy and his BBQ joint get caught up in the mix.
episodes.title: Chapter 22

episodes.synopsis: With a military stand-off overseas and potential violence at home, Francis wants to finish off Tusk for good. Claire and Jackie Sharp collide.
episodes.title: Chapter 23

episodes.synopsis: A Special Prosecutor interrogates Francis. Remy Danton tries to keep his options open. Stamper wrestles with his demons.
episodes.title: Chapter 24

episodes.synopsis: Francis finds himself shut out and Claire makes a difficult sacrifice. Stamper tries to regain control.
episodes.title: Chapter 25

episodes.synopsis: Francis faces annihilation while the nation is in an uproar. Stamper must tie up loose ends. Claire feels the cost of ruthlessness.
episodes.title: Chapter 26

episodes.synopsis: A rocky start for the Underwood Presidency. Frank wants to introduce an ambitious jobs program, while Claire sets her sights on the United Nations.
episodes.title: Chapter 27

episodes.synopsis: Claire’s U.N. bid runs into trouble. Frank fights off mutiny with a bold address to the country.
episodes.title: Chapter 28

episodes.synopsis: The Russian president’s state visit becomes a cold war of wills, and some punks heat things up.
episodes.title: Chapter 29

episodes.synopsis: Claire bypasses Russia at the U.N. Frank tries to outmaneuver a potential challenger and ends up face to face with a higher power.
episodes.title: Chapter 30

episodes.synopsis: Frank declares war on Congress to jump-start his jobs program. Claire spars with the Russian Ambassador.
episodes.title: Chapter 31

episodes.synopsis: Frank and Claire travel to Moscow to negotiate the return of an imprisoned U.S. citizen. Claire takes a stand that jeopardizes their plans.
episodes.title: Chapter 32

episodes.synopsis: The damage is done and the Underwoods must repair it. But deep wounds don't heal fast, and sometimes not at all.
episodes.title: Chapter 33

episodes.synopsis: A hurricane endangers more than just the entire East Coast and Frank must make a difficult choice.
episodes.title: Chapter 34

episodes.synopsis: The Jordan Valley erupts in chaos just as Frank's campaign is picking up steam. Claire gets disturbing intel and counsels him.
episodes.title: Chapter 35

episodes.synopsis: Frank needs to deal with Petrov one on one while Claire tries to preserve the peace-keeping mission. Sacrifices must be made.
episodes.title: Chapter 36

episodes.synopsis: Things turn ugly when Frank, Jackie, and Heather square off during their first debate. Tom joins Claire on the campaign trail.
episodes.title: Chapter 37

episodes.synopsis: Heather Dunbar goes for the jugular, forcing Claire to confront her worst fears. The rift between Frank and Claire widens.
episodes.title: Chapter 38

episodes.synopsis: In the midst of the Iowa caucuses, Frank and Claire must confront hard truths about each other.
episodes.title: Chapter 39
